      <prefercite id="aspace_cite">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Misc. Ms. 427, The Charles Henry Kauffman Collection of Materials Relating to Charles Ives in the Irving S. Gilmore Music Library of Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_bh1">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Born in Pennsylvania, Dr. Charles Henry Kauffman practiced osteopathic surgery in Brookfield, Connecticut. Kauffman was a close friend of Charles Ives. The two first met in the 1920s through Ives's brother, Judge J. Moss Ives, and his brother-in-law, the Rev. Joseph Twichell. Dr. Kauffman treated both Charles Ives and his mother for various illnesses, and remained in contact with Ives throughout their lives.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_sc">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Much of the collection pertains to the composer Charles Ives. It includes letters between Kauffman and Ives (as well as other correspondents), published writings and music by Ives, articles concerning Ives, poetry by Kauffman, and a commemorative coin issued in honor of Ives.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_arr1">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into 5 series: I. Correspondence. II. Writings and Music. III. Clippings. IV. Programs. V. Miscellaneous.</p>  
      </arrangement>
